{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17630884","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17630884"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T17:21:09+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T17:21:09+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17335"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"17335","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/17335"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.04,0.12,0,0,0.84]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10025"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78665"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"10025","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/10025"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17335"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64008"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"7181"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"23476"},{"type":"contributions","id":"23478"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78665","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/78665"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe central nervous system is protected by three layers of connective tissue called the meninges.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the correct arrangement of the meningeal layers from superficial to deep?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Arachnoid mater, pia mater, dura mater","Dura mater, subdural space, pia mater","Epidural space, dura mater, pia mater","Arachnoid mater, dura mater, subarachnoid space","Dura mater, arachnoid mater, pia mater"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe meninges are arranged in three distinct layers. The outermost layer is the \u003Cstrong\u003Edura mater\u003C/strong\u003E, which is tough and fibrous. The middle layer is the \u003Cstrong\u003Earachnoid mater\u003C/strong\u003E, and the innermost layer is the \u003Cstrong\u003Epia mater\u003C/strong\u003E, which adheres directly to the surface of the brain and spinal cord.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArachnoid mater, pia mater, dura mater\u003C/strong\u003E - This reverses the correct order\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDura mater, subdural space, pia mater\u003C/strong\u003E - This omits the arachnoid mater and incorrectly lists a space as a layer\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEpidural space, dura mater, pia mater\u003C/strong\u003E - This omits the arachnoid mater and incorrectly includes a space as a layer\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArachnoid mater, dura mater, subarachnoid space\u003C/strong\u003E - This incorrectly orders the layers and includes a space rather than the pia mater\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EImportant spaces exist between these layers: the epidural space (outside the dura), the subdural space (between dura and arachnoid), and the subarachnoid space (between arachnoid and pia). The subarachnoid space contains cerebrospinal fluid.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The meninges consist of three layers from outer to inner: dura mater, arachnoid mater, and pia mater.","The pia mater is a delicate, highly vascular membrane that closely follows all contours of the brain and spinal cord surface."],"references":["Netter FH. Netter Atlas of Human Anatomy: A Regional Approach with Latin Terminology. Eighth edition. Elsevier; 2022.","\u0022Meninges of the central nervous parts\u0022 by SVG by\u00a0Mysid is licensed under\u00a0Creative Commons\u00a0Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported\u00a0license. (https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0) \u003Chttps://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Meninges-en.svg\u003E"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64008"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"17335"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21302"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"21302","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21302"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/wWMvZZX9rGbZ1LSNiLAmvNkld32CMW.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/wWMvZZX9rGbZ1LSNiLAmvNkld32CMW.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":640,"height":416}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"64008","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/64008"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-11T21:46:12+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-01-11T21:46:40+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10025"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"78665"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"